This paper involves the development of an Android program that uses deep learning neural networks to detect live targets from images obtained from an unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV). The paper also implements certain features of the TensorFlow Android Camera Demo application. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). 

Additionally, the paper involves the use of an unmanned aerial vehicle, which falls under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of deep learning neural networks also falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the processing of multimedia data, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
